olive oil
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet jasmine rice
5 cup boiling water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet Asian Greens
2 radish
2 clove garlic
¼ tsp salt
¼ tsp brown sugar
pinch chilli flakes
½ packet Soy Sauce Mix
1 packet Pork Mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 sachet Crispy Shallots

• Boil the kettle.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Add ginger paste and jasmine rice, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Stir in the boiling water(5 cups for 2 people / 10 cups for 4 people) and chicken-style stock powder. Cover with a lid and simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until rice is
tender, 20 minutes.

• Meanwhile, drain sweetcorn.
• Roughly chop Asian greens.
• Thinly slice radish into sticks.
• Finely chop garlic.

• Once rice is tender, remove lid, then stir in sweetcorn and the salt.
• Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, until congee has thickened, 15-20 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add an extra dash of water to your congee if you prefer a thinner consistency

• While congee is thickening, in a small heatproof bowl, combine garlic, the brown sugar and a pinch of chilli flakes (if using).
• In a large frying pan, heat olive oil (1 tbs for 2 people / 2 tbs for 4 people) over high heat, until just smoking, 30 seconds-1 minute, then carefully pour the oil over the garlic mixture.
• Stir in soy sauce mix (see ingredients) until combined. Set aside.

TIP: The hot oil will bubble up and 'cook' the garlic.

• When congee has 5 minutes remaining, return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add sweet soy seasoning, Asian greens and a splash of water, then cook until fragrant and wilted, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide ginger rice congee between bowls.
• Top with Chinese soy pork and radish.
• Drizzle garlic chilli oil over congee.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!